CAIRO: Arab League Secretary-General Ahmed Aboul Gheit held talks with Somali President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud in Cairo. They discussed the latest developments in Somalia and the various challenges facing the country, according to the secretary-general’s spokesman. Aboul Gheit affirmed the Arab League’s readiness to support Somalia in various fields, especially education, health and food security. Somalia is one of the countries most affected by the current drought in the Horn of Africa.